            In response to the noble Lord, Lord Higgins, under that section the matter is decided by the commissioners if the Inland Revenue does not agree with the appellant. Obviously there are transitional arrangements, but even so the ability to accept late
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_216gc' title='Col. 216GC &mdash; HL Deb 28 May 2002 vol 635 c216GC' name='column_216gc' href='#column_216gc' rel='bookmark'>216GC</a>
            appeals continues. I hope that noble Lords are reassured by the fact that current law goes further than the amendment.
